15 TO HONOR CRAIG JONES, LONGTIME CHOIR
16 TEACHER AT HARDING ACADEMY IN SEARCY,
17 UPON THE OCCASION OF HIS UPCOMING
18 RETIREMENT.
19
20 WHEREAS, Craig Jones, teacher and choral director at Harding Academy in
21 Searcy, Arkansas, for forty-eight (48) years, will retire at the end of this
22 school year; and
23
24 WHEREAS, along with serving as choral director, Craig Jones teaches
25 Bible classes at Harding Academy; and
26
27 WHEREAS, Craig Jones is a 1977 graduate of Harding College (now Harding
28 University) and received his master's degree in music history from Memphis
29 State College (now the University of Memphis); and
30
31 WHEREAS, under the direction of Craig Jones, the junior and senior high
32 choirs of Harding Academy have consistently received Division I ratings at
33 regional and state competitions; and
34
35 WHEREAS, under the direction of Craig Jones, the Harding Academy choirs
36 have performed in thirty-eight (38) states; and
