2 WHEREAS, under the direction of Craig Jones, the Harding Academy choirs
3 have performed at Carnegie Hall in New York City, New York, Walt Disney
4 World, Disneyland, the George W. Bush Presidential Library, the United States
5 Air Force Academy, the National September 11 Memorial & Museum, Harding
6 University presidential inaugurations, the United States Capitol, the
7 Louisiana legislature, and the Arkansas State Capitol, and they have sung
8 Ludwig van Beethoven's famous Symphony No. 9 and other notable pieces with
9 the Arkansas Symphony Orchestra; and
10
11 WHEREAS, in 2024, Craig Jones was honored at the Arkansas Chapter of
12 the American Choral Directors Association Trailblazer Awards; and
13
14 WHEREAS, in 2010, Craig Jones was named Teacher of the Year by the
15 National Christian School Association; and
16
17 WHEREAS, Craig Jones received the 2010 Outstanding Music Educator Award
18 from the National Federation of State High School Associations; and
19
20 WHEREAS, Craig Jones has also received many awards from Harding Academy
21 during his career there; and
22
23 WHEREAS, Craig Jones is a past president of the Arkansas Choral
24 Directors Association; and
25
26 WHEREAS, Craig Jones is also renowned as a skilled impressionist,
27 especially of Presidents of the United States,
28
29 NOW THEREFORE,
30 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
31 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
32
33 THAT the House of Representatives honor Craig Jones, longtime choral
34 director at Harding Academy in Searcy, upon the occasion of his upcoming
35 retirement.
